The headquarters of Google is located in Mountain View, California, USA. The complex is known as the Googleplex, and it covers an area of approximately 2.5 million square feet. The Googleplex is home to thousands of employees and includes a variety of amenities, such as cafeterias, fitness centers, and recreational facilities. The campus also features a number of unique design elements, including colorful bikes for employees to ride around the campus and a large Android statue near the entrance.